      "body" : "Brief summary of breadwallet stance on 0-conf:\r\n\r\nWorst case for 0-conf is full-RBF, any tx can be reliably reversed at any time before confirmation. In this case, merchants will *still* accept 0-conf and consider the fraud rate part of the cost of accepting bitcoin. (The cost of waiting for confirmation is even higher in many situations.) Our goal then is to lower that fraud rate as much as practical, even though getting to zero obviously isn't possible",
